Most women in the EU are on birth control, but not all use condoms. For reasons unknown, this was not factored into the Orthodox church’s constitutional amendment.

The accusation that the amendment is correlated with the nosy attitude of some Orthodox male bishops needs to be explained in different associations according to how that religion views contraceptives and abortions. We cannot say that this was the only reason the high religious majority of the government followed through with this action. Having said that, it has contributed in drawing attention to the gradual deterioration of the society.

I do have to ask an entirely different question for all our female readers here. Would you approve if you were told birth control was to be illegal due to the high religious institute of your society?
